-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

WHY CC BY 4.0 WAS CHOSEN FOR THIS PROJECT
------------------------------------------

This design proposal is intended to serve the public good. The goal is to
improve the citizen-facing experience of the Central KYC Records Registry card
issued by CERSAI and the Government of India.

CC BY 4.0 was selected because it:

  1. Permits unrestricted use by government agencies, including CERSAI and any
     department of the Government of India, without any royalty or fee.

  2. Permits modification and adaptation — CERSAI or any authorized agency may
     refine, scale, or evolve this design for production use.

  3. Permits commercial use — print vendors, technology partners, and system
     integrators engaged by CERSAI may use this design without restriction.

  4. Requires attribution to the original creator, ensuring that Pt. Prashant
     Tripathi is credited as the originator of this design concept, consistent
     with the spirit of open and transparent contribution to public services.

  5. Is internationally recognised, legally robust, and widely understood by
     governments, institutions, and open-source communities worldwide.

ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENT
------------------------

Any use, reproduction, adaptation, or implementation of this design must
include the following attribution in a reasonably visible location:

  "CKYC Card Redesign Concept by Pt. Prashant Tripathi
   (https://github.com/PtPrashantTripathi/ckyc-card-redesign-proposal)
   Licensed under CC BY 4.0"

DISCLAIMER
----------

This is an independent, voluntary design proposal. It is not an official
CERSAI design, and it has not been commissioned, endorsed, reviewed, or
approved by CERSAI, the Reserve Bank of India, the Ministry of Finance, or
any other government authority. The CERSAI logo used in this proposal belongs
to CERSAI and is reproduced solely for illustrative purposes within this
design proposal.
